'''''Affectio societatis''''' is the common will of several legal persons or legal entities to merge into one entity.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Qu'est-ce que l'affectio societatis ? - LegaLife|url = https://www.legalife.fr/blog/affectio-societatis/|accessdate = 2015-06-19}} (In French).</ref> It is a key characteristic of a company under [[French law]]. Articles 1832 and 1833 of the [[French Civil Code]]<ref>{{Cite web|title = www.legifrance.gouv.fr/content/download/1950/13681/.../Code_22.pdf|url = http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/content/download/1950/13681/.../Code_22.pdf|website = www.legifrance.gouv.fr|accessdate = 2015-06-19}}</ref> form the basis of this principle, although since there is no statutory definition, it has also been shaped by [[jurisprudence]].

