{{Infobox person | name = Kurban Omarovich Kurbanov | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1980|08|25}} | birth_place = [[Khadzhalmakhi]], [[Levashinsky District]], [[Republic of Dagestan]], [[Russia]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Russian | other_names = | occupation = businessman, blogger | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = }} '''Kurban Omarovich Omarov''' ({{lang-ru|Курба́н Ома́рович Ома́ров}}, born on 25 August 1980) is a Russian entrepreneur and blogger.
== Biography == ===Family=== His father is Omar Omarov<ref name=Howstar/> who is a Merited Builder of Russian Federation. His mother is Shuanet Gadzhiyeva,<ref name=Howstar/> daughter of the historian Bulach Gadzhiyev and granddaughter of [[Magomet Gadzhiyev]], [[Hero of Soviet Union]]. She is a [[solfège]] (music) teacher in college. Omarov has a younger brother Ansar.<ref name=Howstar/>
He married Russian television presenter [[Kseniya Borodina]] on 3 July 2015.<ref name=Howstar>[http://howstar.ru/news/russia-man/Kurban-Omarov-Biography.html Kurban Omarov // Biography - businessman, Kseniya Borodina's husband] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819064010/http://howstar.ru/news/russia-man/Kurban-Omarov-Biography.html |date=2017-08-19 }} {{ref-ru}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://7days.ru/lifestyle/wedding/poyavilos-pervoe-foto-so-svadby-ksenii-borodinoy-i-kurbana-omarova.htm|title = First wedding photos of Kseniya Borodina and Kurban Omarov are released|author = |work = |date = 2015-07-03|publisher = 7days.ru|deadurl = no|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150703184336/http://7days.ru/lifestyle/wedding/poyavilos-pervoe-foto-so-svadby-ksenii-borodinoy-i-kurbana-omarova.htm|archivedate = 2015-07-03|df = }}</ref> He has a son Omar (born on 1 February 2008),<ref name="Woman.Ru"/> a step-daughter Marusya, daughter of Borodina (born on 10 June 2009)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.rambler.ru/starlife/39035255/|title=Kseniya Borodina congratulated the son of her husband on birthday|date=2018-02-01|publisher=[[Rambler (portal)|Rambler]]|language=Russian|accessdate=2018-03-07}}</ref> and daughter Teona "Tenya" (born on 22 December 2015).<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.wday.ru/seks-otnosheniya/novosty/kseniya-borodina-rodila-doch2/|title = Kseniya Borodina borns a daughter|author = Viktoriya Dudina, Olga Turbina|work = |date = 2015-12-22|publisher = Woman’s Day|deadurl = no|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151225073742/http://www.wday.ru/seks-otnosheniya/novosty/kseniya-borodina-rodila-doch2/|archivedate = 2015-12-25|df = }}</ref><ref>[http://www.cosmo.ru/stars/news/25-12-2015/kseniya-borodina-nazvala-doch-boginey/ Kseniya Borodina gave her daughter a name of Goddess // Cosmopolitan] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304135121/http://www.cosmo.ru/stars/news/25-12-2015/kseniya-borodina-nazvala-doch-boginey/ |date=2016-03-04 }}</ref>
=== Youth === Omarov was an amateur boxer who wan several open championships held at [[Makhachkala]]. He attended schools in cities like [[Buynaksk]], [[Makhachkala]], [[Baku]], [[Mineralnye Vody]], [[Bournemouth]], [[London]] and [[Moscow]]. His nickname "Zima" came from his childhood.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cosmo.ru/stars/krupnim-planom/ot-lyubvi-do-nenavisti-istoriya-ksenii-borodinoy-i-kurbana-omarova/|title=From love till hate: story of Kseniya Borodina and Kurban Omarov|language=Russian|date=2016-07-22|publisher=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|accessdate=2018-03-07|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310201511/https://www.cosmo.ru/stars/krupnim-planom/ot-lyubvi-do-nenavisti-istoriya-ksenii-borodinoy-i-kurbana-omarova/|archivedate=2018-03-10|df=}}</ref> He studied management and the economics of civil engineering at [[Moscow State University of Civil Engineering]] in the years between 1997 and 2002.<ref name=Howstar/>
===Business=== Between 2002 and 2010 he worked in his father's firm Zhilishchnaya Iniciativa (Apartment Initiative), a general civil building enterprise.<ref name=Howstar/> He was the manager in a unit of the cottage building in Moscow, Oblast, and apartment repair works in Moscow. Since 1 February 2015 he has been the head of a business unit in a stock company ABC. Omarov is also the manager for solutions development of the [[Smart Home]] software system for commercial release. On 16 September 2015 he founded and trademarked Zima Group, which produces fashionable women's clothing for people between the age of 14 and 49 for the retail trade.
===Blogger=== Omarov is the author of an Internet reality show TGRM, whose episodes were posted on [[Youtube]].<ref name="Woman.Ru">{{cite web|url=http://www.woman.ru/stars/life/article/216052/|title=Kurban Omarov says, "I dated not with Kseniya Borodina, but with girl Ksyusha whom I fell in love with. Her popularity is outside our house|publisher=Woman.ru|date=2018-01-24|language=Russian|accessdate=2018-03-07|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310201102/http://www.woman.ru/stars/life/article/216052/|archivedate=2018-03-10|df=}}</ref> He also has a YouTube channel Отец ({{lang-en|Father}}).<ref>{{YouTube|channel=UCGOEA3QzapnB-rYZKJy6hig|title=Kurban Omarov}}</ref> His [[Instagram]] account has 1.7 million subscribers, and Omarov is in top-30 of the most popular male Russian Instagram bloggers.
